<p>I am trying to convert json to java object.  Given class is:</p>  <pre><code>class Product{     private String name;     private Price price; } </code></pre>  <p>where price is another class:</p>  <pre><code>class Price{     private java.lang.String currency;     private java.lang.String value; } </code></pre>  <p>I am trying to convert following json:</p>  <pre><code>[     {         "name": "test",         "price": {             "value": "1234.00",             "currency": "INR"         }     } ] </code></pre>  <p>While converting json to Price object I am getting error:</p>  <pre><code>Can not set com.google.api.services.content.model.Price field com.google.api.services.content.model.Product.price to java.util.LinkedHashMap </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to register mixIn or another way with Jackson, which tell Jackson that use Price class for attribute price?</p>  <p>Code used to de-serialize:</p>  <pre><code>final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();  final JavaType type = this.objectMapper.getTypeFactory().constructCollectionType(List.class, Product.class); return objectMapper.readValue(new File(filePath), type); </code></pre>